pointsandrectangleslab

Class APRectangle

  • java.lang.Object
    • pointsandrectangleslab.APRectangle

  • public class APRectangle
extends java.lang.Object
    The APRectangle class is an application that finds and sets values of a rectangle, and can print these values. Methods within this class can return values related to the rectangle, and can shrink the rectangle as well. Getter methods can return values like width, height, and the point top left corner, while setter methods can set these values as well. Additionally, this class also contains methods for getting the remaining corner points through use of height, width, and the top left point.

      • getTopRight

        public APPoint getTopRight()
        This class method is used to return a new APPoint for the top right. It does this by declaring a new double yval, getting the y value from the APPoint myTopLeft and getting the x value by declaring a new double called xval, getting the top left x value and adding the value of myWidth. This method must have the prior values for APPoint myTopLeft and myWidth in order to function properly.
        Returns:
        new APPoint(X Value, Y Value) This returns the new point for the top right of the rectangle.

      • getBottomRight

        public APPoint getBottomRight()
        This class method is used to return a new APPoint for the bottom right. It does this by declaring a new double yval, getting the y value from the APPoint myTopLeft plus the double myHeight and getting the x value by declaring a new double called xval, getting the top left x value and adding the value of myWidth. This method must have the prior values for APPoint myTopLeft, myWidth and myHeight in order to function properly.
        Returns:
        new APPoint(X Value, Y Value) his returns the new point for the bottom right of the rectangle.

      • printAPRectangle

        public static java.lang.String printAPRectangle(APRectangle d)
        This method prints out the resulting APRectangle that will be created in the runner class, formatting it as shown in the return. Needs getter methods for getting the width and height in order to function.
        Parameters:
        d - The APRectangle that will be constructed in the runner using the constructor in this class.
        Returns:
        String "[APRectangle (" + d.getWidth() + "," + d.getHeight() + ")]" The String that will return upon calling printAPRectangle.
